Question:
Validate email addresses.
Conditions: must contain @ and ., no spaces, only alphanumeric/underscore/dot before @.

Code:


import re
email = input("Enter email: ")
pattern = r'^[A-Za-z0-9._]+@[A-Za-z0-9.-]+\.[A-Za-z]{2,}$'
if re.match(pattern, email):
    print("Valid Email")
else:
    print("Invalid Email")


Input 1:

test.email_123@gmail.com


Output 1:

Valid Email


Input 2:

wrong email@com


Output 2:

Invalid Email
